INTROPDUCTION TO BASH AND SHELL
SHELL:A shell is a command-line interpreter that provides an interface between the user and the operating system.
Bash (Bourne Again SHell) is a specific shell and is the default shell on many Linux distributions.

BASIC FILE OPERATIONS:
PWD-Print current directory
IS- List files
Mkdir-create dictionary
cp-copy files
cat-display file contents
chmod-file operations
chown-changes the ownership

